## Home Assistant Integration

To integrate the ESP32-C3 LD2410C Presence Sensor with Home Assistant, follow these steps:

1. Open the Home Assistant dashboard.
2. Navigate to Configuration > Integrations.
3. Click on the "+" icon to add a new integration.
4. Search for "MQTT" and select it.
5. Enter the required MQTT broker details (IP address, port, username, password).
6. Save the configuration.

The presence status will now be available in Home Assistant, and you can use it to trigger automations or display occupancy information on your dashboard.
